We can see from the formula that the two values we're missing are $F_y$ and $F_z$.

$\begin{align}
F_y &= 2y = 2 \\ \\
F_z &= 2z = 2\sqrt{2}
\end{align}$

Let's find $F_x$, $F_y$, and $F_z$.

$\begin{align}
F_x &= \dfrac{2x}{2\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} = \dfrac{3}{5}\\ \\
F_y &= \dfrac{2y}{2\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} = \dfrac{4}{5} \\ \\
F_z &= -2z = -2\sqrt{5}
\end{align}$
